cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.AI, cs.NE 

This paper deals with text classification tasks using word embeddings, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses the use of contextual variables and their contribution to the final word vector, which could be related to machine learning (cs.LG), information retrieval (cs.IR), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper proposes a new approach for fine-tuning word embeddings, which could be relevant to neural networks (cs.NE).
